Comments.Message:
I have found a way to correct my issue by adding the following mime type to the mime.types configuration file of Apache :
application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet xlsx

Then I use the following code to generate the file and redirect my browser :
$objWriter->save('my_file.xlsx');
echo('<html><head><META HTTP-EQUIV="Refresh" Content= "0;URL=my_file.xlsx"></head></html>');

If I use $objWriter->save('php://output'); I still receive a file called excel.zip instead of excel.xlsx
